article.headline: Troy 67, South Alabama 55
article.story: HOT SPRINGS, Ark. -- Richard Delk scored 17 points and Brandon Hazzard added 16 to lead top-seeded Troy past South Alabama 67-55 Sunday night in the quarterfinals of the Sun Belt tournament. The Trojans used a 15-0 run to open a 20-point advantage in the first half. Troy (19-11) advances to play two-time defending champion Western Kentucky in the semifinals Monday. Allyn Cooks led ninth-seeded South Alabama (17-15) with 13 points. Troy led 38-21 at halftime. The Jaguars cut the deficit to eight with 6:31 remaining, but Troy's Vernon Taylor caught an airball by Hazzard under the basket and scored to make it 56-46.
